     1.4            M                                       ANTEX VERSION / SYST
A                                                           PCV TYPE / REFANT   
########################################################### COMMENT             
General hint for satellite antenna corrections:             COMMENT             
   All values in this file refer to an IGS-specific axis    COMMENT             
   convention which differs from manufacturer               COMMENT             
   specifications for certain satellite types. The IGS      COMMENT             
   convention allows for a uniform description of the       COMMENT             
   spacecraft attitude for all satellites applying a yaw-   COMMENT             
   steering attitude control. Detailed definitions are      COMMENT             
   provided in Montenbruck et al. (2015).                   COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
GPS satellite antenna corrections:                          COMMENT             
  - z-offsets:                                              COMMENT             
    + satellite-specific                                    COMMENT             
    + based on reprocessed (1994-2020) AC SINEX files       COMMENT             
    + weighted mean of eight ACs (COD, ESA, GFZ, GRG, JPL,  COMMENT             
      MIT, NGS, ULR)                                        COMMENT             
    + solutions aligned to ITRF2020                         COMMENT             
    + trend-corrected to epoch 2015.0                       COMMENT             
    + analyzed and combined by IGN                          COMMENT             
    + L1 and L2 set to the results for the ionosphere-free  COMMENT             
      linear combination                                    COMMENT             
    + block-specific mean values for historical satellites  COMMENT             
      (active prior to 1994)                                COMMENT             
    + BLOCK IIIA satellites: disclosed PCO values           COMMENT             
      adjusted by one common offset in z direction (+89.35) COMMENT             
      (GPS, 2021)                                           COMMENT             
  - phase center variations:                                COMMENT             
    + block-specific                                        COMMENT             
    + purely nadir-dependent (no azimuth-dependence)        COMMENT             
    + maximum nadir angle: 14 degrees (Block I), 17 degrees COMMENT             
      (Block II/IIA/IIR-A/IIR-B/IIR-M/IIF/IIIA)             COMMENT             
    + adopted from igs05.atx                                COMMENT             
    + solutions aligned to IGb00                            COMMENT             
    + unweighted mean of two ACs (GFZ, TUM)                 COMMENT             
    + L1 and L2 set to the results for the ionosphere-free  COMMENT             
      linear combination                                    COMMENT             
    + Block IIF: adopted from igs08.atx, solutions aligned  COMMENT             
      to IGS08, unweighted mean of CODE and ESOC            COMMENT             
    + BLOCK IIIA: based on estimations by ESA and CODE      COMMENT             
    + GPS BLOCK II extension for nadir angles beyond 14     COMMENT             
      degrees based on LEO data from 2009 analyzed by CODE  COMMENT             
    + GPS III extension for nadir angles beyond 14 degrees  COMMENT             
      based on LEO data as described in Conrad et al. 2023. COMMENT             
  - x- and y-offsets:                                       COMMENT             
    + block-specific (except for Block IIR)                 COMMENT             
    + satellite-specific corrections from pre-flight        COMMENT             
      calibrations for Block IIR (Dilssner et al., 2016:    COMMENT             
      Evaluating the pre-flight GPS Block IIR/IIR-M antenna COMMENT             
      phase pattern measurements, IGS Workshop 2016)        COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
GLONASS satellite antenna corrections:                      COMMENT             
  - z-offsets:                                              COMMENT             
    + satellite-specific                                    COMMENT             
    + weighted mean of five ACs (COD, ESA, GFZ, GRG, TUG)   COMMENT             
    + solutions aligned to ITRF2020                         COMMENT             
    + trend-corrected to epoch 2015.0                       COMMENT             
    + L1 and L2 set to the results for the ionosphere-free  COMMENT             
      linear combination                                    COMMENT             
    + block-specific mean values for historical satellites  COMMENT             
      (active between 1998 and 2002)                        COMMENT             
  - phase center variations:                                COMMENT             
    + block-specific (common parameters for GLONASS and     COMMENT             
      GLONASS-M), satellite-specific values for R714        COMMENT             
    + purely nadir-dependent (no azimuth-dependence)        COMMENT             
    + maximum nadir angle: 15 degrees                       COMMENT             
    + adopted from igs08.atx                                COMMENT             
    + solutions aligned to ITRF2008                         COMMENT             
    + unweighted mean of two ACs (CODE, ESOC)               COMMENT             
    + L1 and L2 set to the results for the ionosphere-free  COMMENT             
      linear combination                                    COMMENT             
  - x- and y-offsets:                                       COMMENT             
    + block-specific                                        COMMENT             
    + based on manufacturer information                     COMMENT             
    + time-dependent offsets for dY > 10 cm                 COMMENT             
      (Dach et al. 2019)                                    COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
GALILEO-0A/B satellite antenna corrections:                 COMMENT             
  - x-, y- and z-offsets:                                   COMMENT             
    + satellite- and frequency-specific values based        COMMENT             
      on ESA information (Zandbergen and Navarro, 2008)     COMMENT             
  - phase center variations:                                COMMENT             
    + wild card values                                      COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
GALILEO-1 and GALILEO-2 satellite antenna calibrations      COMMENT             
  - PCO and PV values generated from ARP-related            COMMENT             
    information in ANTEX_GAL_FOC_IOV.atx (GSA, 2016a) and   COMMENT             
    CoM/ARP coordinates (GSA, 2016b) as published by the    COMMENT             
    GSA                                                     COMMENT             
  - z-PCO scale correction:                                 COMMENT             
    + one offset for all Galileo satellites (except E102)   COMMENT             
    + one offset for E102                                   COMMENT             
    + weighted mean of four ACs (COD, ESA, GFZ, GRG)        COMMENT             
    + solutions aligned to ITRF2020                         COMMENT             
    + trend-corrected to epoch 2015.0                       COMMENT             
  - Derived from satellite antenna ground measurements      COMMENT             
    H(f,dir) and ideal Galileo SISICD signal-modulations    COMMENT             
  - PCOs refer to the center-of-mass in accord with IGS     COMMENT             
    ANTEX conventions                                       COMMENT             
  - Carrier-phase patterns refer to the                     COMMENT             
    carrier-phase-center and IGS axes conventions           COMMENT             
  - Signals: E5a,E5b,E5(AltBOC),E6,E1                       COMMENT             
             E5(AltBOC) from E5AQ and E5BQ                  COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
BeiDou satellite antenna corrections:                       COMMENT             
  - BDS-2 C02 and C07 PCOs represent AC- and type means of  COMMENT             
    PCO estimates by F.Dilssner (IGS WS 2014),              COMMENT             
    J.Guo (2106, DOI 10.1007/s00190-015-0862-9),            COMMENT             
    A.Sipthorpe (IGS WS 2016), and                          COMMENT             
    G.Huang (2018, DOI 10.1007/s10291-018-0716-z)           COMMENT             
    based on the ionosphere-free combination of B1I/B2I     COMMENT             
    observations. PCOs for C06 represent synthetic values   COMMENT             
    computed from AC- and type-mean B1I/B3I PCOs such as    COMMENT             
    to obtain the correct B1I/B2I PCO when forming the      COMMENT             
    ionosphere-free combination of the C02/C06 ANTEX PCOs.  COMMENT             
  - BDS-3S PCOs are based on the rounded average of         COMMENT             
    "manfacturer"/"control center" values in                COMMENT             
    Zhao et al. (2018) DOI 10.1007/s10291-017-0673-y and    COMMENT             
    Xu et al. (2018) DOI 10.3390/s18010135                  COMMENT             
    for C101 as well as rounded, type- and                  COMMENT             
    frequency-spcific "control center" values from          COMMENT             
    Li et al. (2019) DOI 10.1007/s00190-018-1144-0.         COMMENT             
  - BDS-3 antenna information is based on band-specific     COMMENT             
    calibrations published by CSNO                          COMMENT             
    (http://www.csno-tarc.cn/en/system/constellation) and   COMMENT             
    (http://www.csno-tarc.cn/en/datacenter                  COMMENT             
        /satelliteparameters (Status 2022/08/09)),          COMMENT             
    complementary PRN-SVN-IntSatID associations as given    COMMENT             
    in the IGS satellite metadata SINEX file, and estimated COMMENT             
    z-PCOs of the IGS BDS-3 satellite antenna calibration   COMMENT             
    campaign. Missing information for the latest GEO        COMMENT             
    satellites has been copied from GEO-1 (C217).           COMMENT             
    + block-specific estimated B1C/B2a phase patterns from  COMMENT             
      COD, ESA, GFZ, SHA, TUM, WHU with extrapolation to    COMMENT             
      15 deg for BDS-3 MEO satellites                       COMMENT             
    + block-specific estimated B1C/B2a phase patterns from  COMMENT             
      COD, SHA, TUM, WHU with extrapolation to 10 deg for   COMMENT             
      BDS-3 IGSO satellites                                 COMMENT             
    + Retained x/y-PCOs and B1 z-PCOs from CSNO/TARC        COMMENT             
    + Adjusted B2 and B3 z-PCOs of BDS-3 MEO and IGSO       COMMENT             
      satellites to obtain SVN-specific B1C/B2a and B1I/B3I COMMENT             
      z-PCOs aligned to IGS20 as estimated by CAS, COD,     COMMENT             
      GFZ, GRG, JGX, SHA, TUM, WHU (B1C/B2a) as well as     COMMENT             
      DLR and WHU (B1I/B3I)                                 COMMENT             
    + Multiple intervals are considered for selected SECM   COMMENT             
      satellites with time-varying PCOs. In this case, no   COMMENT             
      PCOs are provided prior to 01-Jan-2021                COMMENT             
    + Preliminary z-PCOs of C232 and C233 are based on      COMMENT             
      copied CSNO vales of C228 and IGS estimates           COMMENT             
    + Preliminary z-PCOs of C234 and C235 are based on      COMMENT             
      copied CSNO vales of C225 and DLR estimates only      COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
QZSS satellite antenna calibrations                         COMMENT             
  - PCO and PV values generated from S/C-origin related     COMMENT             
    phase center and center-of-mass information published   COMMENT             
    by the CAO (CAO, 2017)                                  COMMENT             
  - Replaced J001/J002/J004 z-PCOs by estimated values      COMMENT             
    from ionosphere-free L1/L5 linear combination aligned   COMMENT             
    to IGS20, weighted average of COD, GFZ, JGX, TUM        COMMENT             
  - PCOs refer to the center-of-mass in accordance with IGS COMMENT             
    ANTEX conventions                                       COMMENT             
  - Carrier-phase patterns refer to the                     COMMENT             
    carrier-phase-center and IGS axes                       COMMENT             
  - PV information for QZS-1 is presently unavailable       COMMENT             
  - Signals: J1, J5                                         COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
QZSS satellite antenna corrections:                         COMMENT             
  - x-, y- and z-offsets:                                   COMMENT             
    + satellite-specific                                    COMMENT             
    + frequency-specific                                    COMMENT             
    + based on JAXA information (CAO)                       COMMENT             
    + values refer to the main L-ANT antenna (consideration COMMENT             
      of the SAIF antenna requires an extension of the      COMMENT             
      ANTEX format for signal-specific values)              COMMENT             
  - phase center variations:                                COMMENT             
    - Signals: J1, J5                                       COMMENT             
    + maximum nadir angle: 10 degrees                       COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
IRNSS satellite antenna corrections:                        COMMENT             
  - x-, y- and z-offsets:                                   COMMENT             
    + block-specific                                        COMMENT             
    + based on ISRO information (provided by A.S. Ganeshan) COMMENT             
  - phase center variations:                                COMMENT             
    + wild card values                                      COMMENT             
    + maximum nadir angle: 14 degrees (taking into account  COMMENT             
       the off-nadir pointing navigation antenna)           COMMENT             
                                                            COMMENT             
Receiver antenna corrections:                               COMMENT             
  - absolute elevation- and azimuth-dependent corrections   COMMENT             
    from robot calibrations in the field performed by       COMMENT             
    Geo++ GmbH (https://www.geopp.de/antenna-calibration/)  COMMENT             
  - absolute elevation- and azimuth-dependent corrections   COMMENT             
    from chamber calibrations as performed by the           COMMENT             
    University of Bonn, Institute of Geodesy and            COMMENT             
    Geoinformation                                          COMMENT             
  - purely elevation-dependent corrections from relative    COMMENT             
    field calibrations performed by NGS and/or other        COMMENT             
    institutions; converted to absolute corrections by      COMMENT             
    adding                                                  COMMENT             
      d_offset (AOAD/M_T_abs - AOAD/M_T_rel)  and           COMMENT             
      d_pattern (AOAD/M_T_abs - AOAD/M_T_rel)               COMMENT             
    (https://geodesy.noaa.gov/ANTCAL/,                      COMMENT             
     https://files.igs.org/pub/station/general/igs_01.pcv)  COMMENT             
  - IMPORTANT hints:                                        COMMENT             
    If no corrections are available for a combination of an COMMENT             
    antenna with one specific radome, the values for the    COMMENT             
    corresponding antenna without a radome (radome code:    COMMENT             
    NONE) are used within the IGS.                          COMMENT             
    If no corrections for the GLONASS or GALILEO            COMMENT             
    frequencies are available, do not use those             COMMENT             
    observations                                            COMMENT             
